page.title: 06Environment,Geog.,Ecology
page.content: Our block ranges from{90m to 300m {above sea level}at an outcrop of {Jurassic sandstone.}This is one of three in the area from which outstanding views,including the northern part of the{N.Y.Moors Nat. {Park,}can be obtained.The{North Sea}is only{14kms away. Our block is mainly agricultural with {17% being conifer forest. 8% of our {block is residential. Being{mainly rural}it provides a number of{natural and man made {habitats}and consequently supports a wide variety of{plant and animal life. An animal species list would include {roe deer,badger}and{fox. Birds}would include{woodcock,stonechat}and {buzzard.}On the moors are the three main types of heather, and the forest supports a large number of{fungi, {mosses}and{lichens.
